commit.message:
Test Python 3.8 too (#19)

* Test Python 3.8 too

* Update noxfile.py

Sort input file list (#17)

so that _cmark.so builds in a reproducible way
in spite of indeterministic filesystem readdir order.

See https://reproducible-builds.org/ for why this is good.

Make Python information more explicit in the README (#16)

The tagline "Python bindings for GitHub's cmark"
is already used in the github repository metadata.
This change applies the same working to the README title
and adds similar information to its content.

Add travis test for 3.7 (#12)

* Add travis test for 3.7

* Add sudo and dist to travis.yml
